TRANSCENDENT X: THE FALLEN KING (Sovereign of the Hollow)

Role: Swarm Commander / Legion Architect
Ultimate Attribute: The Boss (Immune to all debuffs and status effects)
Template: Arsenal + Stage

––––––––––––––––––––––––––

1) THE KING’S ACTIVE COMMANDS

1. Commanding Lead
Summons 8 Necrotic Skeletons in rapid succession (0.25s delay between each summon).

2. Troop Deployment
Summons a squad of 6 elite reinforcements.
• Possessed Armors / Corrupted Fallens – 35% chance
• Fallen Heroes / Fallen Giants – 15% chance

3. The Foil, the Épée, and the Sabre
A three-stage sword combo with increasing range.
Final hit is a 360-degree circular strike dealing damage and applying a 6-second Stun.

4. Fallen Comet
Global-range purple spikes rain down across the battlefield.
Deals heavy damage and applies a 5-second Stun.

––––––––––––––––––––––––––

2) AWAKENED FALLEN KING: FALLEN APEX (The Sovereign Legion)

Role: Swarm Commander / Legion Architect
Ultimate Attribute: The Boss (Immune to all debuffs and status effects)

Trigger:
Essence Level 40
No Fallen troops remaining on the field

Effect:
Fallen King transforms into Awakened Fallen King
The Fallen Octet rise simultaneously as Apex variants
Battlefield enters Apex Phase

1. AWAKENED FALLEN KING – COMMAND CORE
Abilities:
Dramatic Entrance: Appears from sky, shockwave stuns towers for 5s, 200 damage to units
Abominable Barrage: Slams sword, summons purple spikes, stuns towers 5s, 50 damage to units
Cataclysmic Cleavings: Three sword slashes (last = full circle), stuns towers 6s, 100 damage to units
Army of Chaos: Summons Fallen Giants (40%), Fallen Shields (20%), Fallen Heroes (40%)
Undead Horde: Summons 8 Necrotic Skeletons (0.25s delay between each)
Complete Awakening: Triggered when 500,000 HP lost; throws shield, stomps → stuns towers 4s; doubles movement speed
Troop Respawn: Slowly restores all fallen troops over time. But does not use them while being awekened.

2. THE FALLEN OCTET – APEX VARIANTS

Rules:
1 unit per Octet member (Boss attribute)
Stronger than base versions
Do not consume 40-weight field limit
If any die, they do not respawn, weakening Apex phase

Name	Role	Core Ability	Attributes
Fallen Warden:	      Tank	        Necrotic Cone / Shield Rush / Mini-Super Surge	Bloated, Tank, Health Regen
Fallen Accelerator:	  DPS	          Laser Beam (overheats if fired too long)	Bloated, Nimble
Fallen Necromancer:	  Controller	  Necrotic Beam / Grave Summon / Grave Spawn	Bloated, Health Regen
Fallen Medic:	        Support	      Link Shot / Healing Pulse / Boosted Link	Bloated, Health Regen
Fallen Mortar:	      Thrower   	  Rocket Barrage / Cluster Bomb / Nuclear Strike	Bloated, Nimble
Fallen Cowboy:	      Assassin	    Dual Shot / Rapid Fire / Shadow Dash	Bloated, Nimble
Fallen Ranger:	      Marksman  	  Explosive Shot / Piercing Charge / Full Charge	Bloated, Nimble
Fallen Templar:	      Ranged Anchor	Heart Laser: 3.5s laser, stuns enemies 2s, attack range 20	Bloated, Health Regen, Boss, Corpse

3. APEX PHASE MECHANICS

Weight Limit: 40-weight applies only to regular troops (King + Octet exempt)
Death of Octet Members: Weakens Awakened Fallen King’s summons/damage
Corpse Mechanic: Fallen Templar leaves a corpse that acts as a shield wall
Apex Decay: Every 20s: small HP regen loss or reduced damage; if ≥4 Octet members die → Apex phase collapses

––––––––––––––––––––––––––

3) GLOBAL LEGION RULE

Global Legion Capacity: 40 Weight
The Fallen King can command units whose combined Weight does not exceed 40.
Stronger units consume more Weight, preventing swarm overload.

Exceptions:
• Fallen Honor Guard: Hard cap of 1 (ignores weight rules)
• Fallen Summoner: Hard cap of 2 (still consumes weight)

––––––––––––––––––––––––––

4) THE LEGION REGISTRY (By Essence Level)

[EL 5] Fallen Dregs (The Vanguard)
Weight: 1
Stats: Faster than average; slightly higher durability
Attributes: Bloated

[EL 7] Fallen Squire (The Guardian)
Weight: 2
Stats: High HP; 29% damage reduction; slower than average
Attributes: Bloated, Nimble, Aggro, Tank, Boss

[EL 13] Fallen Soul (The Ghost)
Weight: 1
Stats: Very high speed; average HP
Attributes: Bloated, Hidden

[EL 14] Fallen (The Soldier)
Weight: 1
Stats: Higher HP and speed than baseline soldiers
Attributes: Bloated, Nimble, Health Regen

[EL 16] Fallen Giant (The Heavy)
Weight: 4
Stats: Massive scaling HP; average speed
Attributes: Bloated, Nimble, Aggro, Health Regen, Boss

[EL 17] Fallen Hazmat (The Immune)
Weight: 2
Stats: High HP; slightly above-average speed
Passive: Total Isolation (20% damage reduction; immune to Fire, Frozen, Knockback, and Stun)
Attributes: Bloated

[EL 19] Fallen Possessed Armor (The Knight)
Weight: 3
Stats: Fast; massive HP while armor is intact
Trait: Becomes Hidden when armor breaks (<50% HP)

[EL 20] Fallen Skeleton (The Thrall)
Weight: 1
Stats: Low HP; very high speed
Attributes: Bloated

[EL 20] Fallen Necromancer (The Summoner)
Weight: 4
Hard Cap: 2 Units
Stats: High HP; slow movement
Ability: Reanimate (Summons up to 10 Skeletons or Necrotic Skeletons)
Attributes: Bloated, Health Regen

[EL 21] Corrupted Fallen (The Elite)
Weight: 3
Stats: High HP; fast movement; 10% natural damage reduction
Attributes: Bloated, Nimble, Health Regen

[EL 22] Fallen Seraph (The Aerialist)
Weight: 2
Stats: Average HP
Attributes: Bloated, Nimble, Flying

[EL 24] Fallen Jester (The Trickster)
Weight: 3
Stats: High HP; 20% damage reduction
Ability: Devious Tricks (Grants nearby allies Nimble or Bloated)
Attributes: Bloated

[EL 25] Fallen Hero (The Brave)
Weight: 3
Stats: Decent HP; 15% damage reduction; immune to Stun
Attributes: Bloated, Nimble

[EL 26] Fallen Necrotic Skeleton (The Greater Thrall)
Weight: 1
Stats: Stronger version of Fallen Skeleton
Attributes: Bloated, Nimble

[EL 28] Fallen Rusher (The Striker)
Weight: 2
Stats: Extremely fast; has a physical shield
Trait: Loses speed when shield breaks
Attributes: Bloated, Nimble

[EL 30] Fallen Shield (The Juggernaut)
Weight: 5
Stats: Massive HP; 20% damage reduction
Passive: Unstoppable (Immune to Knockback, Stun, and Frozen)
Trait: Gains speed when shield is destroyed
Attributes: Bloated, Nimble, Aggro, Health Regen, Boss

[EL 31] Fallen Tank (The Battering Ram)
Weight: 5
Stats: Very high HP; permanently fast movement
Attributes: Bloated, Nimble, Health Regen

[EL 33] Fallen Angel (The High Seraph)
Weight: 4
Stats: Extremely high HP
Attributes: Bloated, Nimble, Flying

[EL 35] Fallen Honor Guard (The Champion)
Weight: N/A
Hard Cap: 1 Unit
Stats: Highest HP in the legion (excluding the King)
Ability 1: For The Honor (Flail smash, high damage + AoE Stun)
Ability 2: Guard’s Grave (Spectral trail granting allies a 5s speed boost)
Attributes: Health Regen, Boss

[EL 37] Fallen Summoner (The Arch-Necromancer)
Weight: 5
Hard Cap: 2 Units
Stats: Very high HP; slow movement
Ability 1: Rise of the Fallen (Summons 6 units: 65% Necrotic Skeleton, 35% Possessed Armor)
Ability 2: Ghost State (Becomes Hidden at <50% HP)
Attributes: Bloated, Nimble

[EL 39] Fallen Guardian (The Sentinel)
Weight: 4
Stats: High-durability tank wielding a broadsword
Ability: Sword Slash (Wide arc attack that stuns enemies)
Attributes: Bloated, Nimble, Boss

[EL 40] Templar (The Sentinel)
Weight: N/A
Hard Cap: 1 Unit
Attributes: Bloated, Health Regen, Boss
Unique Attribute: Corpse
Ability: Heart Laser (Fires a laser from its exposed heart for 3.5 seconds, which stuns enemies and deals damage to them)
Note: This troop is unlocked when The Fallen King enters his Awekenedd version

––––––––––––––––––––––––––
5) CORE PASSIVES (THE KING)

Bone Armor
• Gains 20% Defense at 80% HP
• Gains 40% Defense at 65% HP
• Gains 60% Defense at 50% HP

Crown of Souls
• Gains 1% Damage Resistance for every 10 active Fallen units on the field

––––––––––––––––––––––––––
6) ATTRIBUTE DEFINITIONS (GLOBAL)

Bloated
• Doubles unit HP
• Increases unit size

Nimble
• Movement speed increased by 100% (2× speed)

Aggro
• Enemies prioritize and lock onto this unit

Tank
• Grants 10% damage reduction

Hidden
• Unit is invisible to standard vision
• Can only be detected by advanced vision or superior technology

Health Regen
• Regenerates 5% of max HP every 2 seconds

Flying
• Cannot be hit by ground-based melee attacks

ULTIMATE ATTRIBUTE: THE BOSS
• Immune to all negative effects and debuffs

Corpse
• When dying, the body stays in the field, acting like a wall or shield


Took inspiration from: Fallen King from Roblox: Tower Defense Simulator
